sections.text: history, defined.Medical history shall mean medical history as defined by the department in its rules and regulations and shall include the race, ethnicity, nationality, Indian tribe when applicable and in compliance with the Nebraska Indian Child Welfare Act, or other cultural history of both biological parents, if available.SourceLaws 1988, LB 372, ยง 22;Laws 1996, LB 1044, ยง 120;Laws 2007, LB296, ยง 71;Laws 2011, LB124, ยง 2.Cross ReferencesNebraska Indian Child Welfare Act, see section 43-1501.
